<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880202-0142 </DOCNO><HL> Quaker Oats Plans Buy-Back </HL><SO> </SO><CO> OAT </CO><IN> BBK </IN><DATELINE> CHICAGO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Quaker Oats Co.'s board authorized the purchase of as many as two million shares of its common stock.    The food, pet food and toy marketer said the buy-back will be made through open market purchases and privately negotiated transactions. The repurchased shares, out of 80 million common shares outstanding, will become treasury shares and will be used for general corporate purposes, the company said.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Quaker Oats closed at $42.625 a share, up 50 cents. </TEXT></DOC>